49
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:38,639
she'll be moving in
with her husband's family.

50
00:06:39,640 --> 00:06:40,550
So?

51
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:45,311
l have to find someplace else to live.

52
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:01,637
l'd like to live with you.

53
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:11,232
Sure.

54
00:07:17,120 --> 00:07:18,872
How will l tell my dad?

55
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:20,796
Tell him what?

56
00:07:21,920 --> 00:07:23,672
About us.

57
00:07:23,760 --> 00:07:24,636
What about us?

58
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:02,997
Would you marry me?

59
00:08:13,760 --> 00:08:15,478
No.

60
00:08:44,280 --> 00:08:46,157
l'm never coming back.

61
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:25,476
Come in, quick.

62
00:09:26,520 --> 00:09:28,351
Your mother drank too much
and threw up all over.

63
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:31,239
l'm so worried about her.

64
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:56,150
Bring her some tea.

65
00:10:47,120 --> 00:10:50,829
Are you hungry?
You want something to eat?

66
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:52,750
Who's that guy?

67
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:55,638
lt was just a pair of earrings!

68
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:57,558
Here, take 'em back!

69
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:07,116
You stole more than that.

70
00:11:07,360 --> 00:11:10,955
l told you l never stole anything!
She gave them to me willingly!

71
00:11:14,040 --> 00:11:16,713
You mean she's willing
to let you freeload off her!

72
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:23,433
- Let's see what you say now.
- Don't hit me!

73
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:29,240
- Huh?
- Stop hitting me!

74
00:11:29,240 --> 00:11:32,038
What's that? Speak up!

75
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:33,950
- Louder!
- l stole 'em!

76
00:11:34,240 --> 00:11:35,878
Louder!

77
00:11:36,040 --> 00:11:36,836
l stole 'em!

78
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:41,639
l'm warning you: Don't let me
catch you around my mother again!

79
00:11:58,120 --> 00:11:59,872
You can get changed now.

80
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:41,117
l left some earrings here.
Have you seen them?

81
00:12:42,120 --> 00:12:44,953
No, but l'll help you look.

82
00:12:48,880 --> 00:12:50,711
Hey, what are you doing?

83
00:13:04,280 --> 00:13:06,077
You like this earring?

84
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:07,952
Keep it.

85
00:13:17,680 --> 00:13:18,510
Hey!

86
00:13:22,400 --> 00:13:24,277
Why just one?

87
00:13:24,440 --> 00:13:26,192
l'll wait for you downstairs.

88
00:13:36,840 --> 00:13:38,637
Where are we?

89
00:13:38,760 --> 00:13:39,590
My place.

90
00:13:40,640 --> 00:13:42,471
When did l say
l'd come home with you?

91
00:13:42,720 --> 00:13:44,392
You never said you wouldn't.

92
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:01,672
You live alone?

93
00:14:05,760 --> 00:14:07,432
ls the rent high?

94
00:14:08,440 --> 00:14:09,350
Forty bucks.

95
00:14:09,480 --> 00:14:10,310
Wow.

96
00:14:10,480 --> 00:14:14,109
My whole family lives in one room
that only costs $28.

97
00:14:19,040 --> 00:14:21,793
You bring girls home often?

98
00:14:24,760 --> 00:14:25,636
Sometimes.

99
00:14:31,440 --> 00:14:35,228
Let's get something clear.
l'll stay, but just for a little while.

100
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:42,871
lt's stuffy in here.

101
00:14:45,040 --> 00:14:47,679
Are there other tenants here?

102
00:14:55,520 --> 00:14:57,272
Why's this room empty?

103
00:14:58,400 --> 00:15:01,119
You like nosing around
other people's places.

104
00:15:04,080 --> 00:15:04,956
Where's the bathroom?

105
00:15:13,680 --> 00:15:15,477
Let's go get something to eat.

106
00:15:15,760 --> 00:15:17,398
Why didn't you say so earlier?

107
00:15:22,480 --> 00:15:24,118
lt's pouring outside.

108
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:25,076
l'd better go now.

109
00:15:26,080 --> 00:15:26,990
Would you take me home?

110
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:36,595
- Why did you come with me then?
- l just promised to stay a while.

111
00:15:36,680 --> 00:15:38,511
What kind of girl do you think l am?

112
00:15:39,520 --> 00:15:41,397
Don't think l just jump
into bed with guys!

113
00:15:41,560 --> 00:15:44,279
Don't think l'll do just anything
for some cheap earrings!

114
00:15:44,520 --> 00:15:47,114
l'm not like those other loose women!

115
00:15:47,360 --> 00:15:49,032
Don't come near me!

116
00:16:21,760 --> 00:16:24,558
Let's see how long
you can go without breathing.

117
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:00,030
- A thief!
- Who's that?

118
00:17:01,040 --> 00:17:01,950
- lt's me.
- My friend.

119
00:17:07,800 --> 00:17:09,631
l've told you many times
not to climb up here.

120
00:17:11,800 --> 00:17:14,439
l don't want that lndian guard
downstairs to hassle me.

121
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:23,038
l didn't know you had a friend here.
l'll be going.

122
00:17:23,280 --> 00:17:25,919
Take the stairs.

123
00:17:26,160 --> 00:17:27,832
ln the window,
out the window.

124
00:17:28,920 --> 00:17:31,673
How come your friend's so strange?
What's he do?

125
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:34,552
Don't ask so many questions.

126
00:17:46,120 --> 00:17:47,997
ls he a thief?

127
00:18:02,480 --> 00:18:04,277
What time is it?

128
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:10,030
About 3:00.

129
00:18:14,080 --> 00:18:15,798
l've gotta go home now.

130
00:18:37,920 --> 00:18:39,751
Will we see each other tomorrow?

131
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:41,672
Maybe.

132
00:18:43,680 --> 00:18:45,511
Then call me.

133
00:18:47,600 --> 00:18:49,352
You have my phone number?

134
00:18:54,240 --> 00:18:56,071
l'll write it down.

135
00:19:09,640 --> 00:19:13,315
Call after 11 :00
or l won't be there.

136
00:19:15,440 --> 00:19:17,158
Here.

137
00:19:19,280 --> 00:19:22,909
Leung Fung-Ying?
Aren't you called Lulu?

138
00:19:23,920 --> 00:19:25,797
My coworkers don't know
my English name.

139
00:19:27,800 --> 00:19:29,631
Call me. You promised, okay?

140
00:19:29,880 --> 00:19:31,518
Okay.

141
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:46,877
l know you won't call.

142
00:19:47,080 --> 00:19:48,798
l will.

143
00:19:51,880 --> 00:19:54,553
You didn't even memorize my number!

144
00:19:54,720 --> 00:19:56,472
You wrote it down.
Why should l memorize it?

145
00:19:56,680 --> 00:19:58,398
What if it gets lost?

146
00:20:01,320 --> 00:20:04,153
l could get lost just as easily.

147
00:20:04,280 --> 00:20:06,120
Don't you dare lose it!

148
00:20:06,120 --> 00:20:08,953
Do it and l'll pour
acid on your face!

149
00:20:12,840 --> 00:20:14,717
Don't ever talk to me like that again.

150
00:20:33,080 --> 00:20:34,880
You're good.

151
00:20:34,880 --> 00:20:36,757
You tamed me.
l have to do as you say.

152
00:20:39,760 --> 00:20:41,557
Aren't you going home?

153
00:20:41,720 --> 00:20:43,472
l'll call you a cab.

154
00:20:54,120 --> 00:20:55,951
Now l don't want to go home.

155
00:21:02,840 --> 00:21:04,592
Stay here then.

156
00:21:07,560 --> 00:21:08,390
Damn you!

157
00:21:39,360 --> 00:21:40,998
Good morning.

158
00:21:41,200 --> 00:21:45,796
You still here?
Don't you have to go home?

159
00:21:45,960 --> 00:21:47,712
You didn't go home yourself.

160
00:21:49,840 --> 00:21:51,558
l'm not talking to you.

161
00:21:52,560 --> 00:21:53,470
Hey.

162
00:21:53,640 --> 00:21:55,392
Have we ever met?

163
00:21:56,440 --> 00:21:58,271
You don't look familiar.

164
00:21:58,480 --> 00:22:03,076
But you'd be the one to know
if you've noticed me somewhere.

165
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:06,913
- What do you do for work?
- Work?

166
00:22:08,960 --> 00:22:11,679
Turn up the radio.

167
00:22:31,080 --> 00:22:33,753
Any idea? Figure it out?

168
00:22:33,960 --> 00:22:35,678
Not yet.

169
00:22:35,840 --> 00:22:37,640
Dance for me again, okay?

170
00:22:37,640 --> 00:22:39,517
You trying to take advantage?

171
00:22:40,640 --> 00:22:43,313
Hey! What's your name?

172
00:22:43,480 --> 00:22:45,232
Call me Mimi.

173
00:23:16,120 --> 00:23:18,793
<l've heard
<there's a kind of bird with no legs.

174
00:23:19,920 --> 00:23:21,672
<All it can do is fly and fly.

175
00:23:21,960 --> 00:23:24,554
<When it gets tired,
<it sleeps on the wind.

176
00:23:26,680 --> 00:23:28,398
